Messages end up in the DLQ after failing `maxReceiveCount` times. The original error context is lost unless you preserve it.

```javascript
// Lambda SQS handler with error context preservation
export const handler = async (event) => {
  const failedRecords = [];

  for (const record of event.Records) {
    try {
      await processMessage(JSON.parse(record.body));
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Processing failed:', {
        messageId: record.messageId,
        body: record.body,
        error: error.message,
        attempts: record.attributes.ApproximateReceiveCount,
      });
      failedRecords.push(record);
    }
  }

  // Partial batch failure — only retry failed records
  if (failedRecords.length > 0) {
    return {
      batchItemFailures: failedRecords.map(r => ({
        itemIdentifier: r.messageId,
      })),
    };
  }
};
```

```bash
